<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-9854] STC doesn&apos;t consider switch-expression type for closure cases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9854</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; foo() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;switch&lt;/span&gt;(1) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; { it &amp;gt; 2 }:
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The STC should recognize the type of the switch expression and infer that it&apos;s looking for an &lt;tt&gt;Integer it&lt;/tt&gt; closure, but it checks against Object instead and won&apos;t compile without an extra &lt;tt&gt;Integer it -&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
